# 2149. Rearrange Array Elements by Sign
PS -Problem Statement:

There’s an array ‘A’ of size ‘N’ with an equal number of positive and negative elements.
Without altering the relative order of positive and negative elements,
you must return an array of alternately positive and negative values.

Input: nums = [3,1,-2,-5,2,-4]
Output: [3,-2,1,-5,2,-4]

#INTUTION
Keep +ve and -ve elements of the array in two diff arrays and and put them alertnatively in ans array
Class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> rearrangeArray(vector<int>& nums) {
        vector<int> arr1;
        vector<int> arr2;
        vector<int> ans;

        int n = nums.size();

        for(int i = 0 ; i< n ; i++){
            if(nums[i]>0){
                arr1.push_back(nums[i]);
            }
        }
        for(int i = 0 ; i< n ; i++){
            if(nums[i]<0){
                arr2.push_back(nums[i]);
            }
        }
        int k=0;
        int j = 0;
        while(j<n){
            ans.push_back(arr1[k]);
            ans.push_back(arr2[k]);
            j = j+2;
            k++;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
